New Records: Travis Head scored a career-best 154 not out, the highest individual score by an Australian in England.
Australia achieved their highest successful ODI chase in England with a score of 317-3.
Key Match Events: Travis Head's unbeaten 154 helped Australia chase down 316.
Ben Duckett scored 95 in England's innings.
Marnus Labuschagne took 3-39 and scored an unbeaten 77.
Adam Zampa took 3-49 in his 100th ODI.
Australia's spinners took nine wickets, slowing down England's run rate significantly.
Post-Match Reflections: Travis Head expressed satisfaction with his performance, stating he plays the game more relaxed now.
England stand-in captain Harry Brook reflected on the team's inability to rotate the strike effectively against spinners.
Australia captain Mitchell Marsh praised the team's decision to bowl spin for the last 18 overs.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Australia's Ben Dwarshuis sustained a suspected pectoral strain and did not return to the field.
The second ODI of the five-match series is scheduled at Headingley on Saturday.
